class Solution {
    public int[] memLeak(int memory1, int memory2) {
        int time = 1;
        while (true) {
            if (memory1 >= memory2) {
                if (memory1 < time) break;
                memory1 -= time;
            } else {
                if (memory2 < time) break;
                memory2 -= time;
            }
            time++;
        }
        return new int[]{time, memory1, memory2};
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(√(memory1 + memory2))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Simulate each second, allocating the next i bits to the stick with more free memory until neither stick can satisfy the demand. The loop runs until the required bits exceed both remaining memories, which happens after roughly √(total initial memory) iterations.

